The Conservatives have surged into a lead in the opinion polls for the first time in two years.

David Cameron's party is now two points ahead of Labour as Ed Miliband faces growing pressure that voters do not seem him as the next Prime Minister.

It is a major boost for the Prime Minister who spent the day on the campaign trail with Boris Johnson, with the two men winning a game of table football, a victory for what Mr Cameron called the Blue Team.

