Mr Johnson - whose term runs to 2016 but would be allowed to continue at City Hall at the same time as serving as an MP - has been linked with a series of safe Conservative seats.

But the former MP for Henley has continually ducked demands to declare his intent to stand in the 2015 general election or in a by-election before then.

Earlier, Mr Cameron had stood on watching while Mr Johnson tried his hand at mixing concrete, telling him: 'You show me how it's done.'

He joked that there were 'a few people' he would willingly bury in some of the finished product.

